text: Stacy Lattisaw (born November 25, 1966) is an American R&B; and gospel singer. Since the 1990s, she has performed only gospel music. Lattisaw's major singles include "Love on a Two-Way Street" and 1989's "Where Do We Go from Here". Lattisaw was born in Washington, D.C.. ==References== Category:Singers from Washington, D.C.
